            <h4 class="post-upperdek">
      POISONING THE WELL    &mdash;
</h4>
            <h1 itemprop="headline">Widely used open source software contained bitcoin-stealing backdoor</h1>
            <h2 itemprop="description">Malicious code that crept into event-stream JavaScript library went undetected for weeks.</h2>
            <section class="post-meta">

  
<p class="byline" itemprop="author creator" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
      <a itemprop="url" href="https://arstechnica.com/author/dan-goodin/" rel="author"><span itemprop="name">Dan Goodin</span></a>
    -  <time class="date" data-time="1543272939" datetime="2018-11-26T22:55:39+00:00">Nov 26, 2018 10:55 pm UTC</time>
</p>


  
</section>        </header>
        <section class="article-guts">
            <div itemprop="articleBody" class="article-content post-page">
                                    
<figure class="intro-image intro-left">
  <img src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/backdoor.jpg" alt="Widely used open source software contained bitcoin-stealing backdoor">
      <figcaption class="caption"><div class="caption-credit"><a rel="nofollow" class="caption-link" href="https://secure.flickr.com/photos/jeremybrooks/2398999602/sizes/z/in/photostream/">Jeremy Brooks / Flickr</a></div></figcaption>  </figure>

  <aside id="social-left" class="social-left" aria-label="Read the comments or share this article">
